This is a simplified version of Tabled Transaction Logic interpreter by Paul 
Fodor. You can find more explanation about the interpreter in the following 
paper:

1- Paul Fodor, Michael Kifer, "Tabling for transaction logic", 
PPDP 2010: 199-208

The minimum required version of XSB for this interpreter is 3.6. (Gazpatcho). 

The simplest way to run the interpreter is as follows:


xsb -e "['tr_shell.P'],find_one('path-to-the-test-directory/test_file.P'),halt."
